    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Titus",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "Eternal life was promised before the world began\u2014The qualifications of bishops are given\u2014Unto the pure, all things are pure.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Paul, a servant of God, and an apostle of Jesus Christ, according to the faith of God's elect, and the acknowledging of the truth which is after godliness;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostles.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Election.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In hope of eternal life, which God, that cannot lie, promised before the world began;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hope.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation, Plan of.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Perfection of; Lying.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Tim. 1:1; Abr. 3:26.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But hath in due times manifested his word through preaching, which is committed unto me according to the commandment of God our Saviour;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To Titus, mine own son after the common faith: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ our Saviour.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For this cause left I thee in Crete, that thou shouldest set in order the things that are wanting, and ordain elders in every city, as I had appointed thee:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Order.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood, Authority; Priesthood, Ordination.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 109
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church Organization; Elder, Melchizedek Priesthood.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 116
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0directed, ordered.",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 150
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If any be blameless, the husband of one wife, having faithful children not accused of riot or unruly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0debauchery or insubordination.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For a bishop must be blameless, as the steward of God; not selfwilled, not soon angry, not given to wine, no striker, not given to filthy lucre;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bishop; Leadership.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Delegation of Responsibility; Stewardship.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0obstinate, arrogant.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But a lover of hospitality, a lover of good men, sober, just, holy, temperate;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hospitality.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0what is good.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0self-controlled. TG\u00a0Temperance.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Holding fast the faithful word as he hath been taught, that he may be able by sound doctrine both to exhort and to convince the gainsayers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 11:21.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0those who deny, contradict.",
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For there are many unruly and vain talkers and deceivers, specially they of the circumcision:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0idle speakers, disputers.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Circumcision.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whose mouths must be stopped, who subvert whole houses, teaching things which they ought not, for filthy lucre's sake.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 6:5; Mosiah 29:40; Alma 11:24.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1518
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "One of themselves, even a prophet of their own, said, The Cretians are alway liars, evil beasts, slow bellies.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0lazy gluttons.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "This witness is true. Wherefore rebuke them sharply, that they may be sound in the faith;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 84:117 (87, 117).",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Not giving heed to Jewish fables, and commandments of men, that turn from the truth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 1:4.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 15:9; Col. 2:22; D&C 3:6 (6\u20137); 45:29; 46:7; JS\u2014H 1:19.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0who reject, repudiate the truth.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Unto the pure all things are pure: but unto them that are defiled and unbelieving is nothing pure; but even their mind and conscience is defiled.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Titus 1:15 Unto the pure, let all things be pure\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Purity.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pollution.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 11:39 (39\u201341). TG\u00a0Mind.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conscience.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 133
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 7:15; 2\u00a0Ne. 19:17; D&C 93:35.",
                        "start": 137,
                        "end": 144
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They profess that they know God; but in works they deny him, being abominable, and disobedient, and unto every good work reprobate.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:21 (21\u201323). TG\u00a0False Prophets; Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 8:2. TG\u00a0Ignorance.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 15:8 (7\u20139).",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 94
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0unfit, worthless.",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
